Title: The Semiclassical Limit for $SU(2)$ and $SO(3)$ Gauge Theory on the
  Torus
Authors: Ambar Sengupta
Comments: 18 pages
Journal-ref: Commun.Math.Phys. 169 (1995) 297-314
\\
  We prove that for $SU(2)$ and $SO(3)$ quantum gauge theory on a torus,
holonomy expectation values with respect to the Yang-Mills measure $d\mu_T(\o)
=N_T^{-1}e^{-S_{YM}(\o)/T}[{\cal D}\o]$ converge, as $T\downarrow 0$, to
integrals with respect to a symplectic volume measure $\mu_0$ on the moduli
space of flat connections on the bundle. These moduli spaces and the symplectic
structures are described explicitly.
